WEBVTT

01:06.107 --> 01:09.360
WOULD YOU LIKE TO MEET
YOUR NEXT BOYFRIEND?

01:12.363 --> 01:14.949
EPISODE 1
THE FUTURES OF YOU AND ME

01:33.093 --> 01:34.010
2 WEEKS AGO

01:34.094 --> 01:35.303
I'm home.

01:37.388 --> 01:38.765
I said I'm home.

01:39.557 --> 01:41.726
Initiating home mode.

01:52.320 --> 01:53.947
There's no place like home.

02:02.747 --> 02:04.165
There are 24 hours in a day.

02:05.917 --> 02:07.293
Six hours of sleep.

02:07.794 --> 02:08.837
Ten hours of work.

02:08.920 --> 02:09.838
COMMUTING: 2 HOURS

02:09.921 --> 02:11.631
Time spent commuting and eating…

02:11.714 --> 02:13.383
EATING: 1 HOUR

02:13.466 --> 02:16.302
Take out all of that, plus washing up,
and I'm left with…

02:16.386 --> 02:17.595
WASHING UP: 1 HOUR 30 MINUTES

02:17.679 --> 02:19.556
…just three and a half hours.

02:20.598 --> 02:23.434
Enough to watch a movie or two, at best.

02:25.728 --> 02:30.567
I don't waste those precious
three and a half hours on just anyone.

02:39.117 --> 02:43.079
An ordinary day like today,
with no plans or special events…

02:43.788 --> 02:44.873
So warm.

02:55.592 --> 02:58.011
Days like these are the best kind for me.

02:58.511 --> 02:59.679
Off to sleep now.

03:00.221 --> 03:02.473
Initiating sleep mode.

03:15.028 --> 03:17.113
When the brief happiness ends,

03:17.197 --> 03:19.991
my body is thrown back
into the bustling world.

03:26.122 --> 03:28.708
The circle route train is arriving.

04:13.169 --> 04:16.464
Last summer in the Philippines
was the best.

04:18.091 --> 04:19.759
I wish I could go swimming.

04:21.135 --> 04:22.679
When is summer coming?

04:37.944 --> 04:39.070
Excuse me.

04:40.989 --> 04:42.031
Yes?

04:42.115 --> 04:43.658
I think that kid just…

04:51.666 --> 04:53.960
Damn, that little rascal!

05:00.258 --> 05:01.551
Doors opening.

05:07.598 --> 05:09.142
Doors opening.

05:14.772 --> 05:16.482
Doors closing.

05:18.943 --> 05:19.777
Hello.

05:20.945 --> 05:21.779
Hey.

05:26.200 --> 05:27.285
Come on.

05:28.911 --> 05:29.871
That won't work.

05:32.874 --> 05:33.708
Okay.

05:36.044 --> 05:37.211
What's his deal?

05:38.629 --> 05:40.465
Doors opening.

05:45.428 --> 05:47.180
Doors closing.

05:53.269 --> 05:54.479
UNREGISTERED ID

05:54.562 --> 05:56.564
Please try again.

06:08.284 --> 06:09.118
Producer?

06:09.702 --> 06:10.536
Hello.

06:10.620 --> 06:11.871
-You're here.
-Hi.

06:11.954 --> 06:13.498
Congratulations.

06:13.581 --> 06:15.500
-What for…
-Congratulations.

06:20.588 --> 06:21.631
Thank you.

06:25.259 --> 06:27.762
As always,
another perfectly punctual arrival.

06:27.845 --> 06:30.807
Your commitment to never being early
is truly impressive.

06:31.307 --> 06:33.142
Is it Park Kyeong-nam's birthday today?

06:33.226 --> 06:34.394
Oh, that?

06:34.477 --> 06:37.063
-He signed an adaptation deal.
-Again?

06:37.146 --> 06:40.858
Just come to dinner. The director
is treating us to beef because of that.

06:40.942 --> 06:42.151
Company dinner?

06:43.611 --> 06:45.571
I actually have plans today.

06:45.655 --> 06:47.865
Plans, you say?

06:47.949 --> 06:49.951
Just say you're going vegetarian instead.

06:50.034 --> 06:53.246
Mr. Park will be coming, won't he?
He's the man of the hour.

06:53.329 --> 06:55.206
Even he wouldn't sit this one out.

06:55.706 --> 06:57.041
Are you really not coming?

06:57.542 --> 07:02.088
The director is totally miffed
that you've been skipping dinners lately.

07:02.171 --> 07:04.173
It's not like I'm the only one. That guy…

07:04.674 --> 07:06.634
Producer Park always skips them too.

07:06.717 --> 07:09.554
You have a point.
He's a tiny bit less personable than you.

07:09.637 --> 07:11.431
Don't you think he's so charming?

07:12.432 --> 07:13.433
Huh?

07:15.810 --> 07:18.729
Leave her be.
She's been fangirling over Kyeong-nam.

07:20.106 --> 07:21.357
-Fangirling?
-Yes.

07:21.858 --> 07:24.694
After much deliberation,
I've decided to give liking him a go.

07:26.863 --> 07:29.866
What are you talking about?
You've decided to what? Why?

07:29.949 --> 07:31.409
He's so handsome.

07:33.828 --> 07:34.704
Smells good too.

07:34.787 --> 07:36.038
Oh my.

07:37.165 --> 07:40.418
Eun-ju, you've still got much to learn.

07:40.501 --> 07:41.335
About what?

07:41.919 --> 07:46.340
"Never date someone on your own turf,
even with a knife at your throat."

07:46.424 --> 07:47.633
No one told you that?

07:48.759 --> 07:51.637
Well, I never said I wanted to date him.

07:54.849 --> 07:56.267
You'll know when you know.

07:56.350 --> 07:58.394
-Good luck, Eun-ju.
-Oh dear.

08:01.856 --> 08:02.690
PARK KYEONG-NAM

08:02.773 --> 08:06.068
Here is the requested feedback
on your team's proposal from last week.

08:06.652 --> 08:08.404
Oh, right.

08:09.947 --> 08:10.865
Weaknesses.

08:10.948 --> 08:12.950
The protagonist lacks compelling appeal.

08:13.034 --> 08:14.952
An insufficient grasp
of the fantasy genre.

08:15.036 --> 08:17.705
Disconnected characters
and unclear themes.

08:17.788 --> 08:20.625
The story offers
neither universality nor plausibility.

08:20.708 --> 08:22.919
Strengths. None worth mentioning.

08:31.761 --> 08:33.596
Hey, Cho!

08:34.096 --> 08:37.141
Hey, I'm not done talking to you!

08:41.354 --> 08:42.188
Well,

08:42.730 --> 08:43.856
I'm done working here.

08:44.774 --> 08:46.943
-Wait, Mr. Cho!
-Hey! You're quitting?

08:47.026 --> 08:48.903
-That's right!
-Come on now.

08:48.986 --> 08:50.780
-Let go.
-You know how he is!

08:50.863 --> 08:52.532
-I don't care.
-Just think it over.

08:52.615 --> 08:53.616
No. Move aside!

08:53.699 --> 08:56.118
Mr. Cho! Wait a minute. Mr. Cho!

08:57.286 --> 08:58.704
Is he seriously leaving?

09:04.001 --> 09:06.879
Why are you all looking at me?
I didn't do anything wrong.

09:08.130 --> 09:10.967
Did he really go? What do we do now?

09:11.050 --> 09:12.468
JI-YEON

09:12.552 --> 09:15.388
We really need to meet up today.
I'm serious.

09:15.471 --> 09:16.722
What's up with her?

09:20.393 --> 09:21.477
Hey.

09:21.978 --> 09:22.979
Seo Mi-rae!

09:24.021 --> 09:25.481
It took me ages to get here.

09:29.235 --> 09:31.737
Did you call me here
just to drag me around shopping?

09:31.821 --> 09:34.740
Of course not.
You know I know your lifestyle.

09:34.824 --> 09:38.494
I called you here to address
a very serious and important issue.

09:38.995 --> 09:41.247
Issue? What is it?

09:42.665 --> 09:44.667
An Da-yeong's wedding.
What are you wearing?

09:46.085 --> 09:46.919
Huh?

09:48.254 --> 09:52.049
You're not just going to send her money
and be done with it, are you?

09:52.842 --> 09:55.261
I mean, I'm busy with work and all--

09:55.344 --> 09:57.513
Hey! All the more reason to go.

09:57.597 --> 10:01.434
You should be there, dressed to kill,
to show everyone that you're going places!

10:01.517 --> 10:02.852
I'm going places?

10:03.352 --> 10:05.313
I mean, that's how you should look.

10:05.396 --> 10:07.148
All our classmates are gonna be there.

10:07.231 --> 10:11.068
You can't just sit and watch You-mi
and Se-june pull that lovey-dovey crap.

10:11.152 --> 10:14.530
Breaking them up isn't an option,
but you should still strut your stuff.

10:14.614 --> 10:16.282
"I'm totally doing well right now."

10:16.365 --> 10:17.366
"I'm at my peak."

10:17.450 --> 10:22.246
Hey, it's been forever since we broke up.
Besides, I have nothing to brag about.

10:22.330 --> 10:24.373
Hey, this one looks decent.

10:24.457 --> 10:26.000
Go try this one on.

10:26.667 --> 10:27.710
Hurry up!

10:35.718 --> 10:38.721
It's not even Kim Se-june's wedding.
She's so dramatic.

10:43.434 --> 10:46.270
Don't you dare return that.
I'm so gonna get you.

10:46.354 --> 10:49.440
Oh, please! You're making it sound
like you bought it for me.

10:49.523 --> 10:52.735
Hey, I'm an art teacher.
You think I'm rolling in cash?

10:52.818 --> 10:55.279
I wish I could get you stuff like that.

10:57.698 --> 10:59.700
Mi-rae, you poor thing.

11:00.451 --> 11:02.578
Hey, why would you say that?

11:03.079 --> 11:05.831
I'm doing well. I'm happy, you know.

11:05.915 --> 11:07.083
Aren't you lonely?

11:07.667 --> 11:08.793
Not one bit.

11:11.170 --> 11:14.507
You don't think about guys at all?
For real?

11:14.590 --> 11:17.843
Would my company give me a raise
if I got myself a boyfriend?

11:17.927 --> 11:19.053
Doubt that.

11:19.136 --> 11:22.807
Doesn't that mean dating someone
would only tire me out more

11:22.890 --> 11:24.308
and make me poorer?

11:24.892 --> 11:27.186
Getting physically tired
isn't the only problem.

11:27.269 --> 11:31.816
You know how mentally exhausting it can be
if you end up with an immature guy.

11:31.899 --> 11:35.027
Then find yourself a mature guy!

11:35.111 --> 11:37.446
Or someone exactly like you.

11:38.030 --> 11:40.324
What, a guy like me?

11:40.408 --> 11:41.409
Yeah!

11:41.492 --> 11:44.078
-You know, your kind.
-What kind?

11:44.161 --> 11:48.249
You don't exactly bother others,
but you come off as kinda

11:49.208 --> 11:50.710
standoffish.

11:51.293 --> 11:52.753
Date a guy like that.

11:53.254 --> 11:54.255
Damn.

11:55.297 --> 11:56.716
I'm done working here.

11:56.799 --> 11:58.217
Wait, Mr. Cho!

11:58.300 --> 12:00.010
-You know how he is.
-I don't care.

12:00.094 --> 12:01.762
What are we gonna do without you?

12:01.846 --> 12:03.639
Whatever. Ask the director!

12:03.723 --> 12:05.641
Hey! Are you out of your mind?

12:05.725 --> 12:07.309
Why would I do that?

12:07.393 --> 12:10.980
A person's got to be personable.
That's what makes us human.

12:12.231 --> 12:14.275
So you know how I feel about you!

12:20.614 --> 12:22.283
Hey, I'm home.

12:24.660 --> 12:26.162
I said I'm home!

12:26.662 --> 12:28.539
Initiating home mode.

12:47.767 --> 12:50.936
God, I must have been out of my mind.

13:09.246 --> 13:10.331
Are you serious?

13:10.414 --> 13:11.248
Oh my God.

13:11.749 --> 13:15.002
What a shame. Mr. Cho was so close
to becoming team leader.

13:15.836 --> 13:17.087
Was it because of Yun Song?

13:17.963 --> 13:19.799
Man, who's going to take that on?

13:19.882 --> 13:20.716
PLANNING TEAM 2

13:20.800 --> 13:23.385
Did they find a replacement?
Will Team 1 be taking over?

13:24.470 --> 13:25.471
Word is,

13:25.971 --> 13:28.808
they're considering
Park Kyeong-nam or Seo Mi-rae.

13:29.683 --> 13:32.186
What? I get Park Kyeong-nam.

13:32.269 --> 13:34.814
But Mi-rae?
She's not even in charge of Yun's genre.

13:34.897 --> 13:36.857
The romance producers
are refusing to do it.

13:38.150 --> 13:40.402
Mi-rae's schedule is lighter right now.

13:41.570 --> 13:42.780
Good morning.

13:46.325 --> 13:48.410
What? What is it?

13:59.505 --> 14:00.506
What?

14:00.589 --> 14:01.757
Me? Me? Me?!

14:06.053 --> 14:08.138
Morning, everyone!

14:08.222 --> 14:09.265
Good morning!

14:09.765 --> 14:10.683
Good morning.

14:14.144 --> 14:16.981
Still, Park Kyeong-nam's been doing
better than you lately.

14:17.064 --> 14:19.400
The director might assign him
instead of you.

14:21.443 --> 14:24.697
Well, you never know.
Who knows what the director is thinking?

14:29.785 --> 14:30.911
Don't worry about it.

14:33.622 --> 14:35.124
Oh God.

14:38.168 --> 14:39.545
Ms. Yun!

14:41.463 --> 14:42.506
Ms. Yun!

14:42.590 --> 14:44.758
Please open the door, Ms. Yun!

14:46.760 --> 14:50.097
Ms. Yun! Please give me the final files!

14:50.180 --> 14:52.182
Ms. Yun!

14:59.440 --> 15:01.025
Ms. Yun!

15:02.026 --> 15:02.902
YUN SONG

15:07.406 --> 15:09.158
WEBTOON "THE MAN TO KNOW"
EPISODE 21

15:12.119 --> 15:12.953
UPLOAD COMPLETE

15:16.415 --> 15:20.002
Like a flu virus that slips past
even the raging white blood cells,

15:20.502 --> 15:24.798
Yun Song, back in the day,
completely took over my daily life.

15:30.512 --> 15:31.889
YUN SONG

15:36.101 --> 15:37.269
Yes, Ms. Yun.

15:37.353 --> 15:38.520
Ms. Seo?

15:41.273 --> 15:43.567
Ms. Yun, are you crying?

15:44.109 --> 15:45.527
Did you see the comments?

15:46.195 --> 15:48.864
The things they wrote about me!

15:50.574 --> 15:52.993
Ms. Yun, it's 3:00 a.m. right now.

15:53.077 --> 15:56.580
These hateful comments won't stop
until I die, will they?

15:56.664 --> 16:00.209
But why should I?
Why should I be the one to go?

16:00.292 --> 16:02.378
You sons of bitches!

16:04.964 --> 16:05.965
No!

16:06.507 --> 16:08.008
Absolutely not.

16:25.484 --> 16:27.820
IN

16:27.903 --> 16:29.738
Director, it's Seo Mi-rae.

16:29.822 --> 16:31.115
Yes, come in.

16:34.201 --> 16:37.287
I happened to pass by Raturer Macaron
after having lunch.

16:37.371 --> 16:39.123
I know how much you love…

16:44.753 --> 16:47.798
I see you were also here, Mr. Park.

16:47.881 --> 16:51.010
Yes. I also happened
to pass by that place.

16:52.094 --> 16:54.013
Take a seat. We can talk together.

16:57.891 --> 17:00.477
God, that's sweet. Too sweet!

17:00.561 --> 17:02.604
-Have some coffee.
-Okay.

17:06.984 --> 17:08.819
This coffee you got… You got…

17:09.570 --> 17:11.405
-Yirgacheffe.
-You got Cheffe!

17:11.488 --> 17:13.282
Right, Cheffe.

17:14.658 --> 17:19.121
Man, I didn't realize
how sociable you guys are until today.

17:20.164 --> 17:21.498
I need to talk to you about--

17:21.582 --> 17:22.666
Now!

17:23.834 --> 17:26.879
An opportunity like this
won't ever come around again, okay?

17:26.962 --> 17:28.630
Make your case for why

17:29.131 --> 17:34.344
you should be put in charge of managing
Yun Song, Naemo's number-one author.

17:34.428 --> 17:35.929
Right. I'd first like to--

17:36.013 --> 17:40.350
Even though you two heartlessly declined
to attend any of the dinners,

17:40.934 --> 17:42.770
this is no place for personal grudges.

17:42.853 --> 17:46.106
I'll decide based solely on your skills.

17:46.607 --> 17:49.526
So just relax. And speak up.

17:50.110 --> 17:51.361
What I'm saying is,

17:51.445 --> 17:55.074
the right person to manage
our top author is none other than--

17:55.157 --> 17:56.158
I'll step aside.

17:57.785 --> 17:59.870
I may have joined Naemo a bit earlier,

17:59.953 --> 18:04.541
but Ms. Seo's shown she's capable
of managing authors and planning projects.

18:04.625 --> 18:09.046
No matter how I think about it,
I think you should grab that opportunity.

18:09.129 --> 18:10.172
All right, then.

18:10.255 --> 18:13.634
No. I wouldn't dare take the place
of someone so competent

18:13.717 --> 18:16.303
and manage Ms. Yun for the second time.

18:16.386 --> 18:17.596
You're being too modest.

18:17.679 --> 18:21.391
Mr. Park gets a hit
out of every author he manages.

18:21.475 --> 18:23.310
He'd be perfect for Ms. Yun.

18:23.393 --> 18:26.271
Besides, in his own words,

18:27.022 --> 18:29.483
my projects have
no strengths worth mentioning.

18:31.026 --> 18:34.947
Ms. Yun's already set the whole table,
so there's not much to worry about.

18:35.030 --> 18:38.075
Wow, then you should sit at that table
and dig in.

18:38.158 --> 18:39.118
Enough.

18:40.327 --> 18:44.915
So, neither of you wants to do it.
That's the gist of it, no?

18:47.334 --> 18:48.794
Fine, I get it.

18:51.255 --> 18:52.256
But still,

18:52.339 --> 18:55.467
how can you work in the webtoon business
with so little passion?

18:57.094 --> 18:59.346
You guys worship work-life balance,
don't you?

19:00.139 --> 19:01.598
Forget it. We're all done here.

19:04.101 --> 19:05.185
Seo, you manage her.

19:06.353 --> 19:07.187
What?

19:07.271 --> 19:09.731
I noticed
you were only managing six authors.

19:09.815 --> 19:10.858
But--

19:10.941 --> 19:15.320
Besides, you're the one who directed Yun
toward romance when she started out.

19:15.404 --> 19:18.782
Yes, but I ended up handing it over
to a different producer.

19:18.866 --> 19:20.117
You know it's not my genre.

19:20.200 --> 19:21.577
Actually, I don't.

19:22.286 --> 19:25.289
Then I'll consider this matter settled
and take my leave.

19:25.372 --> 19:27.666
-I have a meeting to attend.
-Sure. Go ahead.

19:27.749 --> 19:28.584
All right.

19:29.209 --> 19:30.210
I'll leave you to it.

19:34.548 --> 19:35.549
Excuse me.

19:41.430 --> 19:43.015
A meeting just magically popped up?

19:44.600 --> 19:45.851
Off you go.

19:54.484 --> 19:55.652
You call that a meeting?

19:58.947 --> 19:59.907
How did it go?

20:04.369 --> 20:05.370
So it's you?

20:08.624 --> 20:11.752
Park Kyeong-nam showed up
with a whole box of macarons.

20:12.377 --> 20:14.379
-Wonder who tipped him off.
-What?

20:15.088 --> 20:16.965
Hey, it wasn't me.

20:17.549 --> 20:19.092
Well, so,

20:19.676 --> 20:22.221
how long will you be
in charge of Ms. Yun Song?

20:24.014 --> 20:25.974
-Dunno.
-How long?

20:26.058 --> 20:28.602
Until she collapses from exhaustion.

20:29.228 --> 20:31.146
Mi-rae, you've got this.

20:31.230 --> 20:34.233
Don't let it get you down.
You just need to get the jump on her.

20:34.316 --> 20:36.235
Like that will work with Yun Song.

20:36.985 --> 20:40.906
Some pasts come back to you,
reborn as the future.

20:41.406 --> 20:42.491
Didn't I tell you?

20:42.574 --> 20:45.244
My sister's friend works
at Dongseoyang Law Firm.

20:45.327 --> 20:47.496
-I'm heading there tomorrow.
-You just got back?

20:47.579 --> 20:49.414
-Stupid online trolls.
-What?

20:49.498 --> 20:52.709
-I'm gonna confront them this time.
-Be quiet. Ms. Yun's on the phone.

20:52.793 --> 20:54.586
Settlement? Not on your life.

20:54.670 --> 20:56.421
-Does she ever sleep?
-I have money.

20:56.505 --> 20:58.840
-I'm calling my sister now.
-She's really something.

21:02.427 --> 21:03.387
She hung up!

21:04.721 --> 21:06.473
I'm really going crazy.

21:06.556 --> 21:08.100
Are you sure you can come tonight?

21:09.184 --> 21:11.270
You bet. It's your birthday.

21:11.353 --> 21:14.022
The advertisement we talked about,
is it a go or not?

21:14.106 --> 21:15.857
You don't need to worry too much.

21:15.941 --> 21:18.277
Of course I need to worry.
We're talking money here.

21:18.360 --> 21:20.112
I'll sort it out, Ms. Yun.

21:20.195 --> 21:23.740
I've been so busy writing.
I can't do anything, let alone eat.

21:23.824 --> 21:25.284
Do you know how hard that is?

21:25.367 --> 21:27.035
I know how hard it must be.

21:27.119 --> 21:29.162
-Can I take a break this month?
-What?

21:29.246 --> 21:31.581
But you already took a break last month.

21:31.665 --> 21:35.794
Why do those damn trolls keep
driving me crazy over every little thing?

21:35.877 --> 21:37.713
It's so frustrating!

21:38.213 --> 21:39.798
Don't mind those hateful comments.

21:47.097 --> 21:48.515
SE-JUNE

21:53.228 --> 21:57.316
The person you are calling is unavailable.
Please leave a message.

22:06.533 --> 22:07.743
SE-JUNE
12 MISSED CALLS

22:07.826 --> 22:08.660
Crap!

22:14.291 --> 22:15.459
Oh no.

22:17.586 --> 22:18.587
Come on!

22:28.221 --> 22:32.601
That's how my romance became a past
that would never come back.

22:36.480 --> 22:40.067
Forget clocking out on time.
You'll be lucky to catch the last train.

22:40.150 --> 22:45.489
Didn't you get a bald spot here before
from stressing about Yun Song?

22:45.572 --> 22:47.074
Let's see if it's grown back.

22:47.157 --> 22:49.368
-She did?
-I think it was around here.

22:50.369 --> 22:53.246
-Was it this side?
-It's gonna fall out again anyway.

22:53.789 --> 22:56.041
Hey, guys. Cut it out.

22:57.125 --> 22:59.044
You had something to tell me, Hye-bin?

22:59.544 --> 23:00.629
Oh, yeah…

23:02.714 --> 23:05.425
Will you be attending
the meeting with the author?

23:16.603 --> 23:18.105
That hurts!

23:18.647 --> 23:21.191
My goodness, I'm sorry! I didn't mean to.

23:21.274 --> 23:22.609
Miss, are you okay?

23:29.825 --> 23:32.744
-She's so pretty!
-Yes. You've gotten prettier.

23:32.828 --> 23:33.745
What a glow-up.

23:33.829 --> 23:35.497
Have you lost weight?

23:36.498 --> 23:40.043
What the heck?
Hey, I told you not to return that outfit.

23:40.127 --> 23:42.629
-I didn't return it.
-Then why didn't you wear it?

23:43.422 --> 23:47.259
No reason. I didn't feel like it.
There's no point in looking good today.

23:47.342 --> 23:49.636
-But--
-Seo Mi-rae!

23:49.719 --> 23:51.513
Hey, you only answer Ji-yeon's calls!

23:51.596 --> 23:53.723
Didn't think I'd see you.
I heard you were busy.

23:53.807 --> 23:55.142
It's so nice to get together.

23:55.225 --> 23:56.351
How have you been?

23:56.435 --> 23:58.270
I've got so much to tell you.

23:58.353 --> 24:00.021
Let's talk over drinks later.

24:00.564 --> 24:01.398
Let's go.

24:01.481 --> 24:02.691
Please welcome the groom!

24:12.200 --> 24:16.872
The cliché of awkwardly running into
your ex at a mutual friend's wedding

24:18.331 --> 24:20.333
never happened, after all.

24:20.417 --> 24:24.087
Today's true star will be entering now.
Please welcome the bride.

24:27.549 --> 24:28.967
Da-yeong!

24:29.676 --> 24:31.511
-Congratulations!
-Beautiful.

24:39.352 --> 24:41.354
Congratulations!

24:41.438 --> 24:43.106
Congrats. Be happy!

24:43.190 --> 24:44.816
You look great together!

24:46.359 --> 24:47.569
You look like a goddess!

24:54.117 --> 24:55.577
She was stunning, wasn't she?

24:55.660 --> 24:57.037
-Yeah.
-She really was.

24:57.120 --> 24:59.873
We'll be having drinks later.
You're coming, right?

24:59.956 --> 25:02.459
Definitely. I'll make sure
to bring Mi-rae along.

25:02.542 --> 25:03.627
-Good.
-Be right back.

25:03.710 --> 25:05.253
You'd better come this time.

25:05.337 --> 25:08.048
-Got it.
-You always skip out.

25:09.508 --> 25:10.759
You-mi!

25:11.259 --> 25:12.427
You-mi! Congratulations!

25:12.511 --> 25:14.513
-Is that You-mi?
-Where?

25:16.014 --> 25:17.265
Hey, you!

25:19.100 --> 25:21.269
-Did you hear? She's getting married.
-Really?

25:21.353 --> 25:22.562
-I am.
-No way!

25:22.646 --> 25:25.941
-Is Se-june still in America?
-Yes. He's coming next week.

25:26.024 --> 25:28.026
Hey, when you get married…

25:30.070 --> 25:35.992
A girlfriend who would be the envy of all,
and a sparkling diamond ring on her hand.

25:42.624 --> 25:48.380
He managed to show off what he had
without even showing his face once.

25:49.172 --> 25:50.799
-Congrats!
-I'm happy for you.

25:50.882 --> 25:53.051
You're even prettier.
Is it the engagement glow?

25:53.134 --> 25:54.970
Stop it! You're all pretty.

26:08.733 --> 26:11.403
I'd love to carry my kid like that
after I get married.

26:12.988 --> 26:14.030
You wanna get married?

26:14.906 --> 26:17.576
-I'm sure I will someday.
-To whom?

26:20.954 --> 26:22.956
Whatever. I'm sure
you'll find someone someday.

26:23.582 --> 26:25.584
Hey, what's up with you?

26:26.251 --> 26:27.294
What do you mean?

26:27.794 --> 26:29.170
Why are you talking like that?

26:29.254 --> 26:32.924
Every time we bring up the future,
you always start with "I."

26:33.883 --> 26:36.303
Have you ever said "we" first?

27:00.452 --> 27:03.955
We haven't met in a while.
Looking forward to catching up tomorrow.

27:04.039 --> 27:06.416
Are you freaking kidding me?

27:06.499 --> 27:08.126
I'd forgotten about this.

27:08.793 --> 27:12.380
Seriously, why are you all
doing this to me?

27:14.174 --> 27:15.383
THE MAN TO KNOW

27:16.551 --> 27:17.886
EPISODE 107

27:17.969 --> 27:20.013
HOW DARE YOU…
MAKE A MOVE ON MY FAMILY?!

27:20.513 --> 27:21.348
SQUEEZE

27:21.848 --> 27:23.767
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
YOU DISAPPOINT ME, AUNT

27:24.267 --> 27:27.937
So she's gone even more off the rails
since the last time.

27:30.357 --> 27:32.859
Naemo's most popular webtoon
for three years running,

27:32.942 --> 27:35.403
Yun Song's The Man to Know.

27:35.487 --> 27:39.407
A chaebol romance featuring Choi Si-woo,
the third-generation heir of SY Group.

27:39.491 --> 27:42.452
Of course, he's just as disrespectful
as he is handsome,

27:42.535 --> 27:46.665
with the classic and clichéd selling point
of only being soft with the female lead.

27:46.748 --> 27:50.877
It's a romance-action hodgepodge mixed
with all the intrigue of a chaebol family.

27:51.378 --> 27:53.588
The main romance plot is so clichéd

27:53.672 --> 27:57.676
that Hans Christian Andersen would rise
from the grave and sue her for plagiarism.

27:58.176 --> 28:00.595
While in Cebu
for a resort construction project,

28:00.679 --> 28:03.723
Choi Si-woo goes surfing one morning,
is swept away by the waves,

28:03.807 --> 28:07.519
only to be rescued by Eun Na-ra,
the female protagonist on vacation,

28:07.602 --> 28:09.938
and falls in love with her.

28:12.899 --> 28:13.733
THE MAN TO KNOW

28:13.817 --> 28:15.026
YS is such a has-been.

28:15.110 --> 28:17.696
Waste of money.
Treat your folks to dinner instead.

28:17.779 --> 28:19.030
How is this number one?

28:19.114 --> 28:20.740
Naemo fell off. Fire YS already.

28:20.824 --> 28:22.492
Manage your authors better.

28:22.575 --> 28:24.953
Great fix for low BP.
It got me all worked up.

28:25.036 --> 28:27.706
YS should quit Instagram first.
I feel sorry for her fans.

28:28.206 --> 28:29.374
YUN SONG

28:30.166 --> 28:32.168
Yun Song debates with readers again.

28:32.252 --> 28:34.796
Yun Song faces backlash
after posting targeted message.

28:34.879 --> 28:37.882
Fans angered by popular author
Yun Song's unprofessional hiatus.

28:54.315 --> 28:55.442
Here for snacks?

28:56.818 --> 28:57.652
No, I just…

29:09.414 --> 29:10.874
That annoying jerk.

29:12.041 --> 29:13.126
That selfish jerk.

29:14.169 --> 29:15.920
That self-centered jerk.

29:16.004 --> 29:18.131
-Ms. Seo.
-Yes?

29:20.216 --> 29:21.551
How long are you gonna be on that?

29:24.637 --> 29:26.556
Just five more minutes.

29:28.641 --> 29:29.476
Sure.

30:08.097 --> 30:09.682
Lovely weather today.

30:17.857 --> 30:20.777
Ms. Seo, about the handover
of Ms. Yun's work…

30:20.860 --> 30:22.779
Oh, right. Who's handing over to me?

30:22.862 --> 30:24.197
From Mr. Park.

30:25.240 --> 30:26.241
Sorry?

30:27.659 --> 30:29.494
Mr. Park?

30:37.085 --> 30:40.296
What was this doing here?
Did you miss it because it's so small?

30:43.049 --> 30:45.301
I'm here for the handover.

30:45.802 --> 30:47.887
Oh, the handover.

30:52.141 --> 30:53.518
Five minutes.

30:54.269 --> 30:55.103
Conference room.

30:56.521 --> 30:58.481
-Five minutes?
-Yes.

31:00.525 --> 31:01.526
All right.

31:08.491 --> 31:12.078
It has the lowest ratings,
but the sales are still steady.

31:12.161 --> 31:14.038
We have three ad deals remaining.

31:14.706 --> 31:17.458
Let's move one to a branded webtoon
by next month.

31:17.542 --> 31:19.252
The CTR is pretty good,

31:19.335 --> 31:21.880
so we can push that point
when contacting future clients.

31:22.463 --> 31:25.675
Bet you feel great after dumping
this ticking time bomb on me.

31:25.758 --> 31:28.094
Could you take a look
at the file I'm sending you?

31:32.807 --> 31:35.310
Man, look how neat his nails are.

31:35.810 --> 31:37.604
Not a single cuticle in sight.

31:37.687 --> 31:38.730
-Ms. Seo.
-Yes?

31:40.857 --> 31:41.858
Please accept it.

31:44.652 --> 31:45.778
Okay.

31:45.862 --> 31:50.158
This is the feedback my team has shared
with Mr. Cho on The Man to Know so far.

31:50.241 --> 31:52.285
-Take a look if you need to.
-Okay.

31:52.785 --> 31:53.786
And…

31:58.166 --> 32:02.253
PARK KYEONG-NAM SENT A MESSAGE
SAUNA COUPON

32:02.337 --> 32:03.171
What's this?

32:04.589 --> 32:06.507
Mr. Cho said you'd need it.

32:08.551 --> 32:11.930
I don't need it.
I'll be sleeping at home, no matter what.

32:13.473 --> 32:15.224
Okay. Sure.

32:16.601 --> 32:19.354
Anyway, that's all for the handover.

32:19.938 --> 32:21.189
Any questions?

32:22.649 --> 32:23.483
No.

32:24.317 --> 32:25.526
Right, then.

32:42.543 --> 32:43.670
Time for lunch.

32:46.214 --> 32:47.215
Is it already?

32:48.508 --> 32:50.218
Today's your first meeting with Yun.

32:51.177 --> 32:53.012
Let's go. I'll treat you to unadon.

32:54.555 --> 32:56.849
You're the best.

33:00.520 --> 33:01.854
-Let's go.
-Let's go!

33:02.355 --> 33:05.525
Eating ginger makes me nauseous
for some reason.

33:05.608 --> 33:07.026
She just doesn't get it.

33:07.110 --> 33:09.445
Ginger is what makes unadon so great.

33:09.529 --> 33:10.947
You got that right!

33:11.948 --> 33:13.992
I'm starving. We could've ordered in.

33:40.268 --> 33:41.185
Seo Mi-rae!

33:42.186 --> 33:44.647
Ms. Yun! You're here early.

33:44.731 --> 33:48.067
We can eat together before our meeting.
I'm right on time, aren't I?

33:48.151 --> 33:50.028
You guys go on ahead!

33:50.111 --> 33:51.696
Come on. I'm hungry!

33:52.739 --> 33:53.948
-Bye, Mi-rae.
-I'm hungry.

33:54.032 --> 33:55.283
Enjoy your meal, Ms. Yun.

34:20.641 --> 34:21.476
It's so good.

34:23.561 --> 34:27.148
-Worried about working with me?
-Sorry? Not at all.

34:28.524 --> 34:31.444
If Cho hadn't gotten sick,
we would have kept going.

34:31.527 --> 34:33.654
It's such a shame he's so frail.

34:33.738 --> 34:37.658
It was our first reunion in a while,
and she was still as clueless as ever.

34:37.742 --> 34:39.619
It's been three years. Let's crush it.

34:40.203 --> 34:43.206
Sure. I look forward to working with you.

34:43.790 --> 34:47.335
If it weren't for you,
things wouldn't have worked out for me.

34:49.796 --> 34:52.715
You would've managed fine without me.

34:53.883 --> 34:54.926
That's true.

35:00.264 --> 35:04.268
The female lead being constantly tormented
by her in-laws' disapproval,

35:04.352 --> 35:07.772
only to have Choi Si-woo swoop in,
acting all cool, to save her…

35:07.855 --> 35:10.525
The readers are getting
a little tired of that.

35:11.234 --> 35:13.402
Recently, the aunt-in-law
has been a bit too…

35:13.903 --> 35:15.029
Good grief.

35:16.197 --> 35:19.450
You want the super-rich, swoony male lead
to drop the cool act?

35:21.702 --> 35:25.456
That wasn't the point.
The constant disapproval of the family--

35:25.540 --> 35:27.959
Why do the readers complain
but keep reading anyway?

35:28.042 --> 35:32.046
Because they just expect me to give them
something to complain about.

35:32.755 --> 35:37.176
Goodness, this is the kind of thing
I was worried about.

35:37.260 --> 35:38.177
Sorry?

35:39.679 --> 35:40.555
What do you mean?

35:41.806 --> 35:44.475
I know you're smart and all,

35:44.976 --> 35:48.396
but we both know we don't really vibe.

35:52.817 --> 35:55.987
Then you could've told the director
you didn't want to work with me.

35:56.737 --> 36:00.658
I mean, it won't be an issue
as long as we figure things out as we go.

36:02.160 --> 36:03.536
Just like old times.

36:09.750 --> 36:10.918
Just like old times.

36:11.002 --> 36:13.588
Please give me the final files!

36:14.088 --> 36:15.423
Just like old times.

36:16.007 --> 36:17.258
Just like old times.

36:17.341 --> 36:18.843
Ms. Yun!

36:21.512 --> 36:25.391
I'm sorry to bother you.
A guest would like to see you, Ms. Yun.

36:25.474 --> 36:27.852
-Is that so? Sure.
-All right.

36:28.352 --> 36:29.520
-Please come in.
-Hello.

36:29.604 --> 36:31.189
-Hi. How have you been?
-Hello.

36:31.272 --> 36:32.231
It's been a while.

36:32.315 --> 36:35.943
This is Producer Seo Mi-rae,
who will be in charge of Ms. Yun.

36:36.027 --> 36:36.944
Right.

36:37.028 --> 36:38.279
-Hello.
-Hello.

36:39.447 --> 36:40.698
My name is Min Jun-young.

36:40.781 --> 36:43.284
-I'm Seo Mi-rae. Great to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

36:43.367 --> 36:44.702
-Have a seat.
-Thanks.

36:46.621 --> 36:50.416
So, there's this new dating simulation
that DU just launched,

36:50.499 --> 36:52.835
and Choi Si-woo was used in it.

36:52.919 --> 36:55.630
Ms. Yun's already met him
a few times over the contract.

36:56.214 --> 36:59.550
If it's a dating simulation,
is it like a game?

36:59.634 --> 37:02.720
It's more like a dating app than a game,
and more realistic.

37:04.513 --> 37:05.848
So what is it called?

37:05.932 --> 37:06.933
Boyfriend on Demand.

37:11.312 --> 37:13.940
See that? I told you she was like this.

37:14.023 --> 37:16.817
She always cringes
at the slightest sign of cheesiness.

37:17.318 --> 37:19.320
-No, that's not it. I--
-That's okay.

37:19.403 --> 37:21.072
Everyone reacts the same way you do.

37:23.324 --> 37:24.992
I wanted to meet you today, Ms. Yun,

37:25.076 --> 37:28.412
because our planning team loved
your character so much.

37:28.496 --> 37:32.500
They suggested using the male leads
from your other works as well.

37:33.459 --> 37:36.087
-The male leads from my other works?
-Yes.

37:37.004 --> 37:40.675
That's understandable,
given Choi Si-woo's popularity,

37:40.758 --> 37:43.594
but the others aren't all that cool.

37:43.678 --> 37:45.972
You could call them Si-woo knockoffs.

37:49.767 --> 37:52.270
-Well, they are!
-Isn't she just hilarious?

37:52.353 --> 37:53.771
What she means is…

37:53.854 --> 37:58.484
Some of us did say other characters
might not have as much impact as Si-woo,

37:58.567 --> 38:03.489
so I just wanted to hear your thoughts
before making a formal proposal.

38:04.699 --> 38:05.950
In that case--

38:06.909 --> 38:09.996
Then how about using the second male lead?

38:11.664 --> 38:14.000
-Yes, that's--
-Second male lead?

38:14.583 --> 38:15.584
Yes, so…

38:15.668 --> 38:20.339
In her works, the lead and the second lead
always have such different charms,

38:20.423 --> 38:22.842
so the female lead wavers
until the very end.

38:22.925 --> 38:23.759
Yes.

38:23.843 --> 38:26.053
Take Hong-ju from Bloodsucking Boyfriend.

38:26.137 --> 38:29.473
He was so popular that you ended up
having to kill him off.

38:29.557 --> 38:30.725
That's right.

38:30.808 --> 38:34.312
Did the Team Leader Say That?
has a final episode rating of four.

38:34.395 --> 38:36.689
Fans of the second lead review-bombed it.

38:36.772 --> 38:37.690
Right.

38:38.566 --> 38:42.903
You could use the second male lead
in your app with this tagline.

38:43.696 --> 38:46.615
"It's your turn to make him the lead."

38:46.699 --> 38:48.909
That would create quite a buzz,
don't you think?

38:48.993 --> 38:50.536
Wow, I love it!

38:51.746 --> 38:53.331
Man, that's just, wow…

38:56.125 --> 38:57.209
"Make him the lead!"

38:58.878 --> 38:59.879
Nice, huh?

39:07.094 --> 39:08.637
Doors opening.

39:09.764 --> 39:12.433
Ms. Yun, please answer your calls
going forward.

39:12.516 --> 39:13.351
Bye now.

39:13.434 --> 39:15.603
-Answer them, please!
-Yeah.

39:23.319 --> 39:24.153
Hi.

39:24.236 --> 39:26.238
Did you have a good talk
with the director?

39:26.322 --> 39:27.239
I did, yes.

39:27.323 --> 39:28.240
Ms. Seo?

39:28.741 --> 39:31.243
Do you have time for a quick chat?

39:32.828 --> 39:33.746
Excuse me?

39:33.829 --> 39:35.498
A product reviewer?

39:35.581 --> 39:37.666
Yes. It's nothing serious, really.

39:37.750 --> 39:39.460
You just need to give us a review

39:39.543 --> 39:42.296
after using the app for a month
with the equipment provided.

39:44.173 --> 39:46.926
I'm not exactly sure
what I should be reviewing.

39:47.718 --> 39:50.930
It's a dating app,
so you'll be reviewing your dates.

39:51.013 --> 39:55.101
Your thoughts on your dates
and what you liked or disliked about them.

39:56.102 --> 39:59.939
So is it more like role-playing
than an actual date?

40:00.022 --> 40:02.024
Very realistic role-playing.

40:02.650 --> 40:05.236
You're not into cheesy stuff,
is that right?

40:06.529 --> 40:07.363
Yes.

40:07.446 --> 40:10.491
Our goal is to captivate
people like you as well.

40:10.991 --> 40:12.993
That, and you seem consumer-savvy.

40:13.577 --> 40:18.624
Our app is in beta service,
so we're in dire need of quality feedback.

40:19.208 --> 40:23.003
You will be compensated,
so think it over and get back to us.

40:24.046 --> 40:25.381
I'd get paid for this?

40:25.464 --> 40:28.634
Of course.
You'd be putting in your valuable time.

40:48.821 --> 40:50.656
"Boyfriend on Demand."

41:15.639 --> 41:18.309
"Sync your phone with the device."

41:25.608 --> 41:29.361
Transmitting user information
to the device.

41:35.826 --> 41:38.913
"Place the ring on your head
and assume a comfortable position."

41:38.996 --> 41:41.749
"The ring will automatically adjust
to the user's head"?

41:41.832 --> 41:44.668
"You are invited to the world of wonders."

41:44.752 --> 41:47.046
Personalization process complete.

41:47.546 --> 41:51.342
Place the ring on your head
and assume a comfortable position.

41:56.430 --> 41:59.141
Press the red button on the device.

41:59.642 --> 42:03.479
When you press the button, the ring
will light up and begin connecting.

42:09.527 --> 42:10.361
What's going on?

42:39.431 --> 42:40.432
It's cold!

43:33.944 --> 43:34.862
I can…

43:35.988 --> 43:37.364
I can breathe.

44:31.293 --> 44:32.503
What the…

44:41.303 --> 44:42.262
Wait a second.

44:43.931 --> 44:45.683
THE MAN TO KNOW

44:46.266 --> 44:47.267
This is…

44:47.351 --> 44:49.269
This is Choi Si-woo.

44:54.400 --> 44:58.195
Congratulations, Ms. Seo Mi-rae,
on meeting your first date!

45:05.202 --> 45:07.079
Are you okay?

48:09.803 --> 48:14.808
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon
